I need to put a lucide react crown component somewhere on this player card so that it looks visually appealing. What do you think I should do?

```tsx Supersixers/components/league/dashboard/Lineup/LineupCards/PlayerCard.tsx
import React from "react";
import { PlayerModel } from "@/models/fixtures/PlayerModel";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"; // If you use a className merge util
import { getSlotColorClasses, getSlotShortCode } from "./styleUtils";
import { Separator } from "@/components/ui/separator";
import Image from "next/image";
import { LineupSwapButton } from "./LineupSwapButton";
import { Arrow } from "@radix-ui/react-hover-card";
import { ArrowRightLeft } from "lucide-react";

// Example props -- adapt as needed
interface PlayerCardProps {
  slotType: string;
  player: PlayerModel;
  round: number;
  isCaptain: boolean;
  isViceCaptain: boolean;
  isSelected: boolean;
  flag: string;
  onCardClick: () => void;
  onSwapClick: () => void;
}

export function PlayerCard({
  slotType,
  player,
  round,
  isCaptain,
  isViceCaptain,
  flag,
  isSelected,
  onCardClick,
  onSwapClick,
}: PlayerCardProps) {
  // e.g., total fantasy points
  const totalPoints =
    (player.points?.[round] ?? 0) + (player.currentMatchPoints ?? 0);

  // e.g., "bg-red-500" or your theme class
  const baseColor = getSlotColorClasses(slotType);

  // e.g., "BAT"
  const shortCode = getSlotShortCode(slotType);

  console.log(shortCode !== "BAT" ? "filter blur-sm" : "");

  return (
    <div
      onClick={onCardClick}
      className={cn(
        // !isSelected ? "filter blur-sm" : "",
        // 3:4 ratio card, uniform shape
        "relative w-full aspect-[3/4] rounded-md overflow-hidden shadow-md filter",
        "cursor-pointer transition-transform hover:scale-[1.02]",
        isSelected ? "ring-2 ring-white-400 ring-offset-1" : "",
        // Apply a base color from your position-based classes
        baseColor,
      )}
    >
      {/* (Optional) overlay to help text stand out */}
      <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20" />
      {/*
        TOP HALF (~50% of card height)
        We'll place the points in the center of the left side,
        and the player image straddling the halfway line on the right.
      */}
      <div className="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2">
        {/* Diagonal or multi-stop gradient */}
        <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 via-transparent to-black/40" />

        <div
          className="
              absolute
              inset-0
              filter blur-[5px]

              bg-[url('https://www.heropatterns.com/svg/topography.svg')]
              bg-repeat
              bg-gray-800/20
            "
        />

        <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20" />
        {/* Points: center of the top-left area (half the width, half the height) */}
        <div className="absolute top-0 left-0 w-1/2 h-full flex items-center justify-center">
          <div className="text-white drop-shadow-md flex flex-col text-center items-center space-y-1">
            <div className="text-2xl font-extrabold">{totalPoints}</div>
            <div className="text-xl"> {player.teamCode} </div>
            <img src={flag} alt="AlT" className="w-9 md:w-10" />
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Player image: anchored at the halfway mark of the entire card */}
        <img
          src={player.imagePath ?? ""}
          alt={player.playerName}
          style={{
            position: "absolute",
            top: "50%", // anchor near the halfway line
            right: 0, // or left: "50%", etc.—up to you
            transform: "translateY(-45%)",
            height: "90%", // 30% of the card's total height
            width: "auto", // auto-calculated width => preserves aspect ratio
            objectFit: "contain",
          }}
        />
      </div>
      {/*
        BOTTOM HALF (~50% of card height)
        Name + Swap button
      */}
      <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2 flex flex-col items-center p-2 justify-between">
        {/* Player Name */}
        <p className="text-sm md:text-lg text-white font-bold drop-shadow-md text-center line-clamp-2">
          {player.playerName}
        </p>

        {/* Role Pill + Swap Button Container */}
        <div className="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-2">
          {/* Role Pill */}
          <div
            className={cn(
              "px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide",
              "text-white shadow-sm border border-white/20",
              baseColor,
            )}
          >
            {shortCode} {/* Add a function to get full position name */}
          </div>

          {/* Swap Button */}
          <button
            onClick={(e) => {
              e.stopPropagation();
              onSwapClick();
            }}
            className={cn(
              "flex items-center justify-center p-2 rounded-full shadow-sm",
              "transition-all transform hover:scale-110",
              "bg-white/20 hover:bg-white/30 border border-white/30",
              "text-white hover:text-white",
              !player.editable && "opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed",
            )}
            disabled={!player.editable}
          >
            <ArrowRightLeft className="h-4 w-4" />{" "}
            {/* Add your swap icon component */}
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

Here are a few suggestions for placing the crown so it feels integrated and not just tacked on. The most common approaches would be:

1. Next to the player’s name (bottom half).  
2. In a top/right corner badge or overlay.  
3. Near the points in the upper half.  

Below is an example of conditionally rendering the crown in the top right corner. (Assuming you’re importing Crown from "lucide-react").

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import { Crown } from "lucide-react";

export function PlayerCard({  
  … // existing props
  isCaptain,
  isViceCaptain,
}: PlayerCardProps) {
  // …

  return (
    <div …>
      {/* Option 1: top right corner with absolute positioning */}
      {(isCaptain || isViceCaptain) && (
        <div className="absolute top-2 right-2 z-10 flex items-center">
          <Crown className="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-400 drop-shadow" />
        </div>
      )}

      {/* 
         Rest of your card content (same as before)
      */}
      <div className="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2">
        …
      </div>

      <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2 flex flex-col…">
        {/* Player Name (Option 2: Show crown next to name) */}
        <p className="text-sm md:text-lg text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center …">
          {player.playerName}
          {(isCaptain || isViceCaptain) && (
            <Crown className="h-4 w-4 text-yellow-400 ml-1 drop-shadow" />
          )}
        </p>
        …
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Which option you choose depends on how you want the captain designation to stand out. If it needs to be very obvious, a top-corner badge can work well. If you’d prefer to keep it subtle, placing it next to the player’s name often feels more natural. Feel free to style it with a slight glow, a tooltip, or any other effect to highlight that it indicates “Captain” or “Vice Captain.”
I chose option 1. I also want to add relavant player stats in a organized and aesthetically pleasing way under the player name. How can I do that?
```ts Supersixers/models/fixtures/PlayerModel.ts
import {
  FirestoreDataConverter,
  QueryDocumentSnapshot,
  SnapshotOptions,
} from "firebase/firestore";

export interface PlayerModelData {
  id: string;
  playerName: string;
  teamCode: string;
  countryID: number;
  teamName: string;
  position: string;
  points: number[];
  currentMatchPoints: number;
  projectedPoints: number;
  player_stats: string[]
  editable: boolean;
  battingAvg: number;
  bowlingAvg: number;
  battingSR: number;
  econRate: number;
  imagePath: string | null;
  battingStyle: string | null;
  bowlingStyle: string | null;
}

export class PlayerModel implements PlayerModelData {
  id: string;
  playerName: string;
  teamCode: string;
  countryID: number;
  teamName: string;
  position: string;
  points: number[];
  editable: boolean;
  currentMatchPoints: number;
  projectedPoints: number;
  player_stats: string[]
  battingAvg: number;
  bowlingAvg: number;
  battingSR: number;
  econRate: number;
  imagePath: string | null;
  battingStyle: string | null;
  bowlingStyle: string | null;

  constructor(data: PlayerModelData) {
    this.id = data.id;
    this.playerName = data.playerName;
    this.teamCode = data.teamCode;
    this.countryID = data.countryID;
    this.teamName = data.teamName;
    this.position = data.position;
    this.points = data.points;
    this.editable = data.editable;
    this.currentMatchPoints = data.currentMatchPoints;
    this.projectedPoints = data.projectedPoints;
    this.battingAvg = data.battingAvg;
    this.bowlingAvg = data.bowlingAvg;
    this.battingSR = data.battingSR;
    this.econRate = data.econRate;
    this.imagePath = data.imagePath;
    this.battingStyle = data.battingStyle;
    this.bowlingStyle = data.bowlingStyle;
    this.player_stats = data.player_stats;
  }

  static playerConverter: FirestoreDataConverter<PlayerModel> = {
    toFirestore: (player: PlayerModel) => {
      return {
        name: player.playerName,
        teamCode: player.teamCode,
        country_id: player.countryID,
        team: player.teamName,
        position: player.position.toLowerCase(),
        points: player.points,
        editable: player.editable,
        current_match_points: player.currentMatchPoints,
        projected_points: player.projectedPoints,
        batting_average: player.battingAvg,
        bowling_average: player.bowlingAvg,
        strike_rate_batting: player.battingSR,
        economy_rate: player.econRate,
        image_path: player.imagePath,
        battingstyle: player.battingStyle,
        bowlingstyle: player.bowlingStyle,
        player_stats: player.player_stats ?? []
      };
    },
    fromFirestore: (
      snapshot: QueryDocumentSnapshot,
      options: SnapshotOptions,
    ): PlayerModel => {
      const data = snapshot.data(options);

      let points = [];

      if (!data.points || typeof data.points === "number") points = [0];
      else points = data.points;

      return new PlayerModel({
        id: snapshot.id,
        playerName: data.playerName || data.name || "", // temp change for dummy data DO NOT USE
        teamCode: data.teamCode || "",
        countryID: data.country_id || 0,
        teamName: data.team || "", // changed to team else it wont display on player dialog as team is what is there in firebase
        position: (data.position || "").toLowerCase(),
        points: points,
        editable: data.editable ?? true,
        currentMatchPoints:
          data.currentMatchPoints || data.current_match_points || 0,
        projectedPoints: data.projectedPoints || 0, // temp change for dummy data DO NOT USE
        battingAvg: data.battingAvg || data.batting_average || 0,
        bowlingAvg: data.bowlingAvg || data.bowling_average || 0,
        battingSR: data.battingSR || data.strike_rate_batting || 0,
        econRate: data.econRate || 0,
        imagePath: data.image_path ?? null,
        battingStyle: data.battingstyle ?? null,
        bowlingStyle: data.bowlingstyle ?? null,
        player_stats: data.player_stats ?? []
      });
    },
  };
}
```


Below is an example showing how you might:

1. Keep the crown in the top-right corner (as in your chosen Option 1).  
2. Organize a small stats section below the player’s name.

This snippet focuses on the bottom half of your card. Note that you can tweak the styling, sizing, and layout as you see fit.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import React from "react";
import { PlayerModel } from "@/models/fixtures/PlayerModel";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
import { getSlotColorClasses, getSlotShortCode } from "./styleUtils";
import { ArrowRightLeft, Crown } from "lucide-react";

interface PlayerCardProps {
  slotType: string;
  player: PlayerModel;
  round: number;
  isCaptain: boolean;
  isViceCaptain: boolean;
  isSelected: boolean;
  flag: string;
  onCardClick: () => void;
  onSwapClick: () => void;
}

export function PlayerCard({
  slotType,
  player,
  round,
  isCaptain,
  isViceCaptain,
  flag,
  isSelected,
  onCardClick,
  onSwapClick,
}: PlayerCardProps) {
  const totalPoints =
    (player.points?.[round] ?? 0) + (player.currentMatchPoints ?? 0);
  const baseColor = getSlotColorClasses(slotType);
  const shortCode = getSlotShortCode(slotType);

  return (
    <div
      onClick={onCardClick}
      className={cn(
        "relative w-full aspect-[3/4] rounded-md overflow-hidden shadow-md filter",
        "cursor-pointer transition-transform hover:scale-[1.02]",
        isSelected ? "ring-2 ring-white-400 ring-offset-1" : "",
        baseColor,
      )}
    >
      {/* Crown in top-right corner for Captain/Vice-Captain */}
      {(isCaptain || isViceCaptain) && (
        <div className="absolute top-2 right-2 z-10">
          <Crown className="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-400 drop-shadow" />
        </div>
      )}

      {/* (Optional) overlay to help text stand out */}
      <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20" />

      {/* TOP HALF */}
      <div className="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2">
        <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 via-transparent to-black/40" />
        <div
          className="
            absolute inset-0
            filter blur-[5px]
            bg-[url('https://www.heropatterns.com/svg/topography.svg')]
            bg-repeat
            bg-gray-800/20
          "
        />
        <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20" />

        {/* Points & Flag */}
        <div className="absolute top-0 left-0 w-1/2 h-full flex items-center justify-center">
          <div className="text-white drop-shadow-md flex flex-col text-center items-center space-y-1">
            <div className="text-2xl font-extrabold">{totalPoints}</div>
            <div className="text-xl">{player.teamCode}</div>
            <img src={flag} alt="Flag" className="w-9 md:w-10" />
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Player image */}
        <img
          src={player.imagePath ?? ""}
          alt={player.playerName}
          style={{
            position: "absolute",
            top: "50%",
            right: 0,
            transform: "translateY(-45%)",
            height: "90%",
            width: "auto",
            objectFit: "contain",
          }}
        />
      </div>

      {/* BOTTOM HALF */}
      <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1/2 flex flex-col items-center p-2 justify-between">
        {/* Player Name */}
        <p className="text-sm md:text-lg text-white font-bold drop-shadow-md text-center line-clamp-2">
          {player.playerName}
        </p>

        {/* Small stats container under name */}
        <div className="flex flex-col items-center text-white text-xs md:text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
          <div className="flex space-x-2">
            <div className="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span className="font-semibold">Bat Avg</span>
              <span>{player.battingAvg.toFixed(2)}</span>
            </div>
            <div className="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span className="font-semibold">Bowl Avg</span>
              <span>{player.bowlingAvg.toFixed(2)}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div className="flex space-x-2">
            <div className="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span className="font-semibold">SR</span>
              <span>{player.battingSR.toFixed(2)}</span>
            </div>
            <div className="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span className="font-semibold">Econ</span>
              <span>{player.econRate.toFixed(2)}</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* (Optionally, show batting/bowling style if you like) */}
          {(player.battingStyle || player.bowlingStyle) && (
            <p className="text-white/70 text-[0.65rem] md:text-xs">
              {player.battingStyle || "—"} / {player.bowlingStyle || "—"}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>

        {/* Role Pill + Swap Button */}
        <div className="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-2 mt-2">
          {/* Role Pill */}
          <div
            className={cn(
              "px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide",
              "text-white shadow-sm border border-white/20",
              baseColor,
            )}
          >
            {shortCode}
          </div>

          {/* Swap Button */}
          <button
            onClick={(e) => {
              e.stopPropagation();
              onSwapClick();
            }}
            className={cn(
              "flex items-center justify-center p-2 rounded-full shadow-sm",
              "transition-all transform hover:scale-110",
              "bg-white/20 hover:bg-white/30 border border-white/30",
              "text-white hover:text-white",
              !player.editable && "opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed",
            )}
            disabled={!player.editable}
          >
            <ArrowRightLeft className="h-4 w-4" />
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Notes on styling:  
• Text sizes (e.g., text-xs, text-sm, etc.) and margins/spacings are just examples. Adjust as needed.  
• If your card height is tight, consider placing fewer stats side by side or using a grid layout.  
• You can also render player.player_stats.map(...) in a wrap-around container if you want more granular stats in pill form.
